title: Colombian rebels who kidnapped Liverpool footballer's dad 'will free him as soon as possible'
description: The father of Liverpool footballer Luis Diaz, who was kidnapped in Colombia, will be freed "as soon as possible", according to a representative of the rebel group holding him.

title: Kenya aims to 'amend' defence agreement with UK after woman's alleged murder
description: One of Kenya’s most senior politicians says moves are under way to "amend" the country’s defence agreement with the UK following the alleged murder of a Kenyan woman by British soldiers.

title: Ordinary life suspended as Israeli military imposes 'lockdown' in West Bank and families flee
description: The sounds of hammering, the deafeningly loud noise of a generator, and the continuous movement of people carrying doors, electrical cables, recovered bricks and even roofs to trucks and trailers.

title: Italy's PM talks of international 'fatigue' over Ukraine war after falling victim to prank call
description: Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni has expressed "regret" after falling victim to a prank call where she acknowledged international "fatigue" over the Ukraine war.

title: British surgeon says he is out 'at last' after spending nearly a month trapped in Gaza
description: A British surgeon who was trapped in Gaza for nearly a month after the conflict between Israel and Hamas broke out has said he is out "at last".

title: Succession star involved in pizza restaurant truck crash
description: Succession star Alan Ruck has been involved in a multi-vehicle collision where a pick-up truck crashed into a Hollywood pizza restaurant.

title: British man arrested in murder probe after woman 'found dead at her home in Italy'
description: A man has been arrested in Leicestershire after a British woman was reportedly found dead at her home in Italy.

title: At least 20 killed at school being used as shelter in Gaza, UN says
description: The UN says a school being used as a shelter has been damaged at the Jabalia Refugee Camp in Gaza, leaving 20 people reportedly dead.
